title.narrative: Integrated HIV/AIDS and TB response in Guinea-Bissau

description.narrative: Guinea-Bissau - TB/HIV - Ministry of Health of the Republic of Guinea-Bissau - MINSAP. This program has the following goals: Reduce the incidence of tuberculosis (TB) by 25 percent and TB mortality by 50 percent by 2020 , compared to 2013. By 2020, Guinea-Bissau will have commenced its transition toward a prosperous, mutually supportive society that guarantees universal access to HIV prevention and AIDS treatment services, in a manner that respects gender and human rights and with leadership . The objectives of this program are: Increase the number of cases of TB (all forms — TBAF) tested from 2,226 in 2016 to 3,599 in 2020. Increase the treatment success rate among new cases of bacteriologically confirmed pulmonary TB by at least 90 percent by 2020. Increase the proportion of TB/HIV patients treated with antiretrovirals (ARVs) from 48.8 percent in 2016 to 95 percent in 2020. Cure at least 70 percent of multidrug-resistant tuberculosis (MDR-TB) patients undergoing second-line treatment by 2020. Seventy percent of the key populations (sex workers [SWs] and men who have sex with men [MSM]) will have adopted less risky behavior by 2020. Seventy percent of the population aged 15 and above, including vulnerable groups (adolescents, young people aged 15-24 years, female street sellers, uniformed service personnel, drivers, fishermen and sailors, migrants and refugees) will have adopted less risky behavior by 2020. High-quality prevention of mother-to-child transmission (PMTCT) services during pregnancy, childbirth and breastfeeding will be provided for 95 percent of HIV-positive pregnant women by 2020. Antiretroviral therapy (ART) will be guaranteed for 90 percent of people living with HIV (PLHIV) (adults and children) who are eligible for treatment, by 2020. ART will be guaranteed for 100 percent of HIV-positive children eligible for treatment. Eighty percent of PLHIV (adults and children) will receive treatment for co-morbidities (TB/HIV, malaria/HIV and hepatitis B or C/HIV) by 2020. Strategic information will be available and used in the national response at all levels. The procurement and supply management (PSM) system will be improved by 2020

title.narrative: Coverage / Output indicator for GNB-C-MOH
Treatment success rate of RR TB and/or MDR-TB: Percentage of cases with RR and/or MDR-TB successfully treated
LAB-Other 1: Percentage of laboratories with adequate quality control performance
Number of TB cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB notified
Percentage of HIV-positive women who received ART during pregnancy and/or labour and delivery
Percentage of pregnant women who know their HIV status
Percentage of adults (15 and above) on ART among all adults living with HIV at the end of the reporting period
Percentage of sex workers reached with HIV prevention programs - defined package of services
Percentage of TB patients with DST result for at least Rifampicin among the total number of notified (new and retreatment) cases in the same year
Percentage of registered new and relapse TB patients with documented HIV status
Number of notified cases of all forms of TB (i.e. bacteriologically confirmed + clinically diagnosed), new and relapse cases
Completeness of facility reporting: Percentage of expected facility monthly reports (for the reporting period) that are actually received
Percentage of HIV-positive new and relapse TB patients on ART during TB treatment
Number of people in contact with TB patients who began preventive therapy
Percentage of men who have sex with men that have received an HIV test during the reporting period and know their results
HRH-Other 1: Percentage of active community health workers who submit monthly reports
Percentage of children (under 15) on ART among all children living with HIV at the end of the reporting period
Timeliness of facility reporting: Percentage of submitted facility monthly reports (for the reporting period) that are received on time per the national guidelines
Number of cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB that began second-line treatment
Percentage of men who have sex with men reached with HIV prevention programs - defined package of services
Percentage of HIV-exposed infants receiving a virological test for HIV within 2 months of birth
Percentage of people living with HIV currently receiving antiretroviral therapy
Percentage of sex workers that have received an HIV test during the reporting period and know their results

Treatment success rate- all forms: Percentage of TB cases, all forms, bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, successfully treated (cured plus treatment completed) among all TB cases registered for treatment during a specified period, new and relapse cases
Percentage of PLHIV on ART who initiated TB preventive therapy among those eligible during the reporting period
